description: Rob runs into Happy Spangler, the fellow who gave him his first break to get into show business. Learning that writing jobs have been a little lean of late for Spangler, Rob decides to repay the debt to his old mentor by agreeing to take him on temporarily as a writer for the Alan Brady Show. Rob soon comes to regret his act of kindness, however, as he realizes that S... Read all
tags: ['character name in title']
synopsis_with_character_names:
Rob (Dick Van Dyke) runs into his old boss Happy Spangler (Jay C. Flippen) while shopping for clothing.

When Rob finds out Hap has been out of the business for fifteen years and is now selling ties, he offers him a job writing comedy with his crew at the Allen Brady show.

Hap deals with the insecurity of trying to write comedy again by telling endless old stories of the days gone by instead of tackling the work.

When the deadline for a new script arrives and the crew is short four minutes Rob can't bring himself to ask his old boss to get to work and quit the reminiscing.

Rob ponders firing his old friend for being more of a distraction than help.

Hap agrees he hasn't been much help says that comedy has changed since the days he wrote. He said that todays audience doesn't buy the old slapstick sketches he liked to write.

As he packs up and is heading out Rob has a change of heart and decides to write that one sketch about the very subject Hap spoke of and that would fill the four minute hole in the show.

Rob demonstrates how Allen Brady would give a lecture at his desk on how comedy has changed and modern audiences are to sophisticated for slapstick while incorporating all the shtick like closing his finger in the desk drawer, impaling himself with scissors and falling out of his chair while giving his talk.

The whole crew agree the sketch is a great idea and they all (including Hap) polish it up for the show.

After the sketch plays well on the show, Hap has to decide to stay on the show or return to retirement.

description: Chip collects items for the school's annual rag drive. One neighbor notices all the strange happenings at the Douglas home. Bub appears drunk, Robbie carries a dummy in the house, and Chip talks to the dummy and drops it out the window.
tags: ['reference to the wizard of oz', 'reference to dorothy gale', 'washcloth', 'washcloth on forehead', 'reference to auntie em', 'wiping forehead', 'wiping cheek with washcloth', 'wiping nose with washcloth', 'wiping forehead with washcloth']
synopsis_with_character_names: Chip (Stanley Livingston) is collecting rags for the school rag drive and asks everyone of his neighbors for their old towels, rags, dresses etc. The elderly new neighbor, Mrs. Pitts (Marjorie Eaton) thinks that his grandfather Bub (William Frawley) is a drunk and unfit for caring for his three grandsons and singing in a drunken manner. When Chip comes to her house to collect rags she keeps him there thinking she is protecting him from an unfit grandfather. She plies Chip with cookies, ice cream and strawberries and cake, giving him something more whenever he tries to leave until he passes out on the couch. In the mean time the family think Chip is missing and starts a frantically search for the young boy Mike and Robbie (Tim Considine and Don Grady) are making a rag dummy out of Bub and they accidentally injure the plumber as Steve helps him inside. Meanwhile, Mrs. Pitts tends to an unconscious Chip, as she wipes his cheek, nose, and forehead with a washcloth and after she exits, he wakes up. In the mean time Mrs. Pitts tells an unbelieving neighbor that Bub is a drunk. When Steve (Fred MacMurray) gets hiccups the neighbors think he drinks too Bub thinks he's nervous he also explains that Mike and Robbie are looking for their baby brother. When a dummy gets made out of the rags is being carried around by Mike and Robbie, Mrs. Pitts is convinced it is Bub passed out. When the dummy falls out of the window Mrs. Pitts thinks it was Bub and passes out. Seeing the Mrs. Pitt carried into the house the neighbor now worries for her safety. She decides to stay. The Douglas's and even Chip are happy.

description: Bub tries to fit into family life, but the boys find things difficult when Bub speaks against a PTA mother, shows up at school with a forgotten lunch, and seems to interfere with girlfriends. Turns out, all the help was needed.
synopsis_with_character_names: At the PTA a worried mother is horrified that softball is dangerous and can hurt the children. She decides to get the game banned from the school playground. Grandpa Bub single handedly takes on the mothers against it feeling the sissy game is harmless. Mike and Robby are left to make dinner and come up with mashed potatoes and toast. Mike is worried about getting a scholarship for college and worries that Bub will ruin his chances with his free spirited talk. Steve comes to Bubs defense with a poignant speech about how Bub left his career to come and take care of his daughters three sons after her death. Chip thinks his Grandpas confrontation with the ladies is neat. The next day Robby is mortified when his Grandfather shows up a drama practice with his forgotten lunch. Then Bub tries to direct the rehearsal, much to the annoyance of the teacher. Robby becomes even more humiliated and goes to his father with his embarrassment over his grandfather. Robby thinks it makes him look like a goof in front of the girl he likes. After the PTA mothers bad mouth Bub to his classmates, Chip is ashamed of his grandfather too. In a surprise turn of events Bub buys Robby a car engine to get him started. Robbys teacher, turns out is very appreciative of Bubs help, Mikes scholarship advisor found Bubs frank talk refreshing and the PTA woman even apologizes for blowing up at Bub.

description: After Steve visits the office of a potential client, a General whose motto is "Adjust or bust," he experiences many transportation inconveniences and missed connections getting home in time for the General's dinner appointment.
tags: ['major general', 'polka dance', 'missed bus stop', 'jalopy', 'falling asleep on a bus', 'car towed', 'car breakdown', 'bus ride']
synopsis_with_character_names: On the day that Steve visits the office of a potential client, a Major General who has a motto of "Adjust or bust," he experiences a series of transportation inconveniences and missed connections. This is made more stressful because the General has told Steve he will come to Steve's house for dinner; Steve is worried that if the General arrives at his house before Steve gets there, the General will be treated as less than a VIP, and Steve will lose the contract. First inconvenience: Steve swaps cars with Mike, and suffers a break-down of Mike's jalopy, having to be towed to a garage. Following this, Steve takes a municipal bus, but sits next to an elderly man who tells him the long, boring story of his life. Not being able to stay alert during this monotonous story, Steve falls asleep, and he misses his bus stop. After Steve gets off the bus, he asks at a nearby house to use the phone, and calls and tells Bub to send Mike over to pick him up. The owner of the house has the idea of marrying off Steve to his eldest daughter, so Steve tells Bub that he will be waiting outside. Mike, who had earlier gone to Steve's intended bus stop to get Steve (who never showed up there), then goes to the house to get Steve, but he is not there. While waiting outside, a bus stopped in front of him, and after talking with the driver, decided to take that bus instead of waiting. Now, Mike goes inside the house, and the owner starts matching him to his youngest daughter. After all of this, we discover that the General had to cancel his plan to eat dinner with the Douglas family, and there was actually no need for Steve to hurry.

description: Steve (Fred MacMurray) enjoys working with a woman engineer (Dorothy Green), who is beautiful. He asks her out for dinner, but she is only interested in work.
synopsis_with_character_names: While at work on a project Steve meets a beautiful woman he is very interested in. Surprisingly she turns out to be a Lady Engineer Dr. Johnson (Dorothy Green) that Steve brought in to work on the project with Steve. Not letting this faze him Steve asks her out to his favorite Italian restaurant. Steve gets there early to make sure for a perfect evening only to find out it is now a tacky Mexican place that plays loud records as music. As Steve bumbles trying to adjust, it turns out that Johnson was there the whole time watching his unsuccessful antics. After working very late into the night on the project (4:02 a.m.to be exact) with Dr. Johnson and the secretary Lucille, Steve asks Johnson to get something to eat. He says that she may be exhausted but still looks fine. The only place open is Freddys Drive In so they go there. They are finished and she is due to leave town. Steve blurts out that he wishes she wasnt leaving because they havent had time to really get to know each other. He wants her to come to dinner at his house to meet his three sons plus Bub is a great cook. She doesnt respond but they kiss and Steve finally asks Johnson for her first name which is Joan. The next morning Steve oversleeps because Bub doesnt wake him up. He frantically calls the hotel and gets the wrong Dr. Johnson. It turns out that Joan has checked out already. As a dejected Steve walks away the camera pans to a note (obviously written by Chip) from Joan. She states that while their timing is off since she is flying off to Washington she hopes that they get another chance at romance.

description: The boys want a raise in their allowance, but Steve tells them that they are spending money recklessly and not doing their chores. Bub has been picking up the slack and doing their work for them. Everyone has bad dreams that night.
synopsis_with_character_names: Its time for bills and Steve comes home to find not only a pile of those but Bub having to do his grandsons chores around the house. Then Steve finds a list of demands from his three sons who not only want their allowance doubled but want other perks such as a trampoline in the back yard. This comes at a bad time as Steve is overwhelmed at the pile of bills. While he always told his sons to write their requests down on paper and then they will discuss it, when they actually do he refuses. Steve gets mad and blows up at his sons who call him unfair and suggests if they dont like the way things are they should go on strike. That night Chip, who has confused labor strikes with baseball strikes dreams that his father physically throws him out of the house and locks the door. Robbie dreams he is in the French Foreign Legion (which his father also suggested) because the whole town turned against the boys. He wakes up to the dog licking his face. Mike dreams he has his father in chains for being unfair and as his father is being attacked he starts screaming for them to stop, Leave him alone, hes my father. We then find Steve spelling out STRIKE on his desk with writing utensils and he is soon dreaming that he comes home to find his sons first frozen and then vanished. Mike comes downstairs and he and Steve try to discuss the money issue which Steve refuses and they argue. Then Steve agrees to extra money for extra work. Mike and his father iron out an agreement. Everyone ends up in the kitchen having a snack with Bub having to clean it all up. He thinks maybe he should go on strike himself.

description: Robbie learns "the grass is always greener on the other side" when he is envious of his friend Hank's home, which seems perfect for a teenager. But Hank is envious of Robbie's life in a happy home and great family.
tags: ['teenager']
synopsis_with_character_names:
Robbie visit's his friend Hank Ferguson's house and is amazed and how much space his friend has. An only child Hank has his own room, phone and everything is in perfect, neat condition. While Robbie resents the wild, noisey house he lives in, Hank hates his solitary home with a mother who lives only to serve him and a father who never wants to come home. When Hank comes to sleep over with Robbie, the Douglas family feels their place must be a let down but Hank loves the lively home. Hank planned to go to boarding school to escape his miserable home life. When his father comes by to check on Hank, he sees the Douglas house full of it's usual uproar but realizes that is what is missing from his home. He orders his wife to go home so they can rethink this house to make it into a home.

In the mean time, Steve (in an especialy brief appearance) decides that Robbie, as a growing teenage boy should have his own room instead of sharing with young Chip. He tries to figure how to convert the basement into Robbie's room only to find out that Robbie is happy the way things are.

She blows up at him for ruining hi fi's for her forever. They make up and dance in the garage as Steve shuts the door.

description: Rick helps Jerry out with the dog.
tags: ['dog', 'animal in episode title', 'dog in episode title', 'violence', 'red haired teenage girl', 'long haired teenage girl', 'blonde woman', 'mother son relationship', 'intergalactic law', 'brown haired teenage girl', 'black haired teenage girl', 'brown haired man', 'evil vs evil', 'freddy krueger spoof', 'incest', 'sadomasochism', 'reference to nightmare on elm street', 'reference to inception', 'recursion', 'dream demon', 'sex party', 'orgy', 's&m', 'monster with breasts', 'jiggling breasts', 'wet dream', 'subconsciousness', 'incest joke', 'grandfather granddaughter incest', 'brother sister incest', 'incestuous desire', 'robot dog', 'slave', 'gun', 'cemetery', 'nightmare', 'dream', 'watching tv', 'talking dog', 'sword', 'whip', 'stewardess', 'mad scientist', 'math', 'parachute', 'plane']
synopsis_with_character_names:
Jerry and Summer are watching TV. Morty's dog Snuffles looks at Jerry, so Jerry opens the door for him, but Snuffles instead pees on the carpet. Morty enters and defends Snuffles, cuddling him, but Jerry takes him and rubs his face in the pee. Rick arrives to take Morty on an adventure, but Jerry demands he first make Snuffles more intelligent. He quickly designs an intelligence-increasing headset, and Snuffles amazes the family with his new obedience. Rick then shows Morty another device that allows him to enter people's dreams. He plans to use it on Mr Goldenfold, Morty's math teacher, to make him give Morty A's. The pair stake out his house, then enter his mind. They find themselves in an airplane, with the hostess being a sitcom character, Mrs Pancake, who flirts with Mr Goldenfold. Rick and Morty pretend to be Islamic terrorists to scare Goldenfold, but he dreams a pair of guns into existence to fight back. Rick reveals they can only leave the dream once Goldenfold naturally wakes up, and if they die in the dream, they die in real life. Back at the house, Summer and Jerry continue to test Snuffles' intelligence. Snuffles attempts to speak. But is unable to communicate effectively. Snuffles discovers that his helmet has multiple empty battery slots, and fills them in.

Back on the plane, Rick takes Mrs Pancake hostage, but another passenger knocks the door open, and everyone falls out. Rick and Morty hang onto Mrs Pancake who retrieved a parachute, but Goldenfold has dreamed into existence a pool of lava that they will fall into. Rick beats Mrs Pancake into unconsciousness, and enters her dream; a sex dungeon. Rick and Morty initially blend in, but upon discovering a sexualised representation of Summer, they become highly distressed and are found out. A centaur attempts to execute them, but Rick strangles him into unconsciousness and they enter his dream. However, the centaur's dream is of a boiler room, and the three are chased by "Scary Terry", a burnt man with miniature swords for fingers. Back at the house, Snuffles builds himself a translator and a robotic arm; Jerry attempts to turn the device off, but Summer prevents him on ethical grounds. Snuffles watches a television program about the history of the dog, and is angered by the systematic breeding of cute, non-threatening dogs.

Back in the dream, Rick and Morty are continually chased, but then find a singing girl. Rick knocks her out and enters her dream; however, they are still in the boiler room, and Scary Terry is able to follow them through the dream layer. Back in the house and later that night, Summer is awoken by Snuffles, wearing a mech suit. He reveals he has renamed himself Snowball, and asks Summer for his testicles. Beth and Jerry enter and try to flee with Summer, but are captured by two other dogs that Snowball had made helmets and mech suits for. Meanwhile in the dream, Rick and Morty escape the boiler room and hide out in a shack. Some time later, Scary Terry gives up the hunt. He heads home, with Rick and Morty following, where they discover he has a wife and son. After he falls asleep, Rick and Morty enter his dream. They discover that he is having a nightmare about being late to school and forgetting his pants, but Rick and Morty defend him against his teachers, and Morty gives him a spare pair of pants. Terry wakes up to see Rick and Morty looking over him, and deduces they too are dream travelers. He makes them breakfast and offers to repay their favor to him, to which Rick asks for help escaping. He takes them through the dream layers by killing each dreamer, causing them to wake up, and finally blowing up Mr Goldenfold whilst screaming "This is because you don't give Morty A's!". Goldenfold decides to give Morty an A.

Rick and Morty head home to discover Snowball turned the house into an arms factory to begin a revolution. Jerry pees on the floor to claim his territory, but Snowball rubs his head in his piss. Snowball cages the family, but offers to make Morty his personal pet. The dogs appear to lead a successful revolution, reversing the human-dog dynamic globally. About a year later, Morty awakes to his life of luxury, but Rick arrives and reveals that they are merely in Snowball's dream; it is still the same night. Rick gives Morty pills to make his kidneys shut down. Snowball expends tremendous amounts of money in finding a cure for Morty, eventually bankrupting his government. He awakes, and having realized that he had become just like the humans, decides instead to take all the dogs of Earth to a new dimension where they could build society from the ground up.

description: It's Christmas. Rick shrinks Morty, injecting him into a homeless man to save Anatomy Park. Jerry tries to have a Christmas free of electronic devices, but regrets his decision when his parents introduce him to their new friend.
tags: ['christmas', 'brown haired teenage boy', 'violence', 'red haired teenage girl', 'long haired teenage girl', 'blonde woman', 'mother son relationship', 'intergalactic law', 'actress voices multiple characters', 'brown haired teenage girl', 'brown haired man', 'evil vs evil', "squeezing a girl's butt", 'reference to jurassic park', 'making out', 'amusement park', 'homeless man', 'dead man', 'disease', 'trapped inside a human body', 'exploding body', 'monster', 'raining blood', 'attractions', 'boyfriend', 'reference to pirates of the caribbean', 'santa suit', 'naked old man', 'hepatitis', 'singing girl', 'lungs', 'intestines', 'defibrillator', 'machine gun', 'sabotage', 'e coli', 'conference call', 'inside body']
synopsis_with_character_names:
Jerry is cooking his Christmas turkey while singing carols, but is disheartened to find Morty, Summer, and Beth all on electronic devices. He asks them to "look alive" for his parents who are shortly arriving, and demands all gadgets go in a stocking. Rick enters with Reuben, a disheveled and unknown man. Jerry questions his motives, but Rick claims Reuben is an old friend he is looking after. Jerry's parents, Leonard and Joyce, arrive with another man named Jakob. Jerry questions Jakob's presence, but Joyce answers vaguely, saying he "helped them both feel alive again". Rick greets them, then asks Morty to join him in the garage. Reuben is on an operating table and in bad shape, suffering from an unknown illness. Rick shrinks an unwilling Morty and injects him into Reuben's chest. Inside, Morty discovers Anatomy Park, an amusement park Rick built inside Reuben. Over the radio, Rick tells Morty to take the train to the liver, which is rundown due to Reuben's alcoholism. Morty is confronted by a large man who questions his presence, and a human-bacteria hybrid arrives and introduces himself as Dr Bloom. Bloom asks Poncho, the large man, to put Morty down once he learns Rick sent him, and introduces his other co-workers, Roger and Annie. Rick, over the radio, asks what's going on, and Bloom reveals that the exhibits have escaped. A monstrous version of Hepatitis A suddenly attacks, causing the party to flee.

Meanwhile at the dinner table, Jerry awkwardly tries to ignore Jakob's presence before asking him about his relationship with his parents. Leonard reveals that Joyce has entered into a polyamorous relationship with Jakob, under Leonard's own blessing. Jerry is unable to contain his disgust at his parents, for which Beth and Summer criticize him. Back in Reuben, the group escape Hepatitis A by entering the lungs, and are joined by a man in a dog mascot suit. Morty climbs several catwalks to investigate the problem, while Bloom discovers that Tuberculosis has been released. Poncho shoots and destroys the bacteria, but severely damages the lungs in the process. As Reuben begins to cough, the group retreats to the digestive system, but the dog man does not make it, and is splattered across Rick's face. Morty tells Rick that Reuben has Tuberculosis, and Rick prepares to cure it, but Reuben dies just before he can. Now trapped inside a dead man, the group try to find an exit. Bloom reveals that the body will begin filling with inert gas and soon become unlivable. To escape, they must reach the colon and its emergency enlarger ray. Bloom reveals to Morty he suspects Annie released the Tuberculosis. Morty unsuccessfully flirts with Annie. Whilst sailing the digestive tract, they are confronted by Gonorrhea. Morty tells Poncho to light a match, igniting the inert gas and exploding Gonorrhea, and the group praise his quick thinking.

In the living room, Summer is leading a drum circle with the family while Jerry sulks in the corner. Beth tries to cheer Jerry up, but he responds sarcastically. A boy named Ethan suddenly enters and reveals himself as Summer's boyfriend. He is mad at her for not responding to his messages, her phone having been confiscated by Jerry. In Reuben, Roger prepares the enlarging ray, while the sphincter dam protecting them from Reuben's waste begins to strain. Morty points out a virus in Poncho's backpack, which Bloom reveals as Bubonic Plague. Poncho holds Annie at knife-point, while revealing that he intends to auction it off. Morty attacks him, freeing Annie and unleashing the Plague, which kills Poncho. As the dam begins to burst, Morty, Annie and Bloom escape, but Roger's foot gets stuck, and he is buried under a deluge of feces.

Back in the house, Jakob talks with Ethan about his past, causing Ethan to break down in tears and forgive Summer, causing Summer to forgive his earlier anger. They make out, as do Jakob and Joyce, causing Jerry to yell at them and storm out. Still in Reuben, Bloom, Morty, and Annie wait inside a theater for further instructions from Rick, their only way out having been destroyed. Morty and Annie make out. Jerry enters Rick's workshop and apologizes for doubting his motives earlier, and his words inadvertently inspire a plan. Rick tells the group to head for Reuben's left nipple, while he sews a stick of dynamite in Reuben's gut and hauls the body into his flying car. Bloom takes Morty and Annie to the bone train, but Bloom needs to remain behind to manually operate the train. As the two leave, Bloom is killed by a group of E. Coli. Rick flies the body into low earth orbit, lights the dynamite, and kicks the body out. He then uses a growth ray to grow Reuben to the size of the US, enlarging Morty and Annie to normal size. On the train, the E.Coli attack, but they fight it off; Hepatitis A reappears and throws the train off the track. Morty and Annie escape the wreckage and flee to the nipple hole, but are still pursued by Hepatitis A. Suddenly Hepatitis C appears, killing A and appearing amicable towards them. Rick arrives in the car and rescues them just as Reuben's body explodes. In the house, the family is unnerved to discover that it is raining blood, and as they crowd Jerry at the TV, the newsman says it "should be fine", leading everyone to relax. Jerry changes his mind about his family, and gives everyone their devices back. Rick laments Bloom's death and the fact that there won't be another Anatomy Park, but Annie claims to be able to recreate it, leading Rick to shrink her. Morty becomes angry, as he thought he had something with her, but Rick says he dodged a bullet. They go to join the family dinner, but discover everyone on their devices. Rick yells at them, but Jerry simply shrugs. Some time later, Rick is building another park inside Ethan, but he becomes angered and abandons the project after the new team attempt to rework Rick's lone contribution, Pirates of the Pancreas.

As Morty arrives at school, Principal Vagina reminds everyone over the loudspeaker that the flu season dance would be held that night. Morty tries to ask Jessica out, but is brushed off by Brad, a jock without a knack for words. That afternoon, Morty speaks with his dad Jerry about love; Jerry consoles Morty that he'll find someone special who likes him back, but Rick interjects that Jerry only married Morty's mother because he got her pregnant, not because of any special bond between them. Rick insinuates that Beth is getting tired in her marriage, and tells Morty that love is nothing more than pointless brain chemicals.

Morty goes to see Rick in the garage, and Rick asks Morty to hand him a screwdriver. But Morty asks him to make him a 'love potion'; Rick initially refuses, but eventually concedes and produces a highly potent goo. Jerry tries to have a serious conversation with Beth, but she has to rush to her veterinary clinic after several injured horses are admitted. She works there alone with Davin, a conventionally attractive man who makes Jerry jealous. At the flu dance, Morty gives Jessica the love potion, who immediately begins flirting with Morty. Brad walks past in shock, and attempts to remove Morty, but Jessica tells him to go away. As she does so, she sneezes, and a little bit of the potion ends up on Brad. Under the potion's influence, he apologizes to Morty, but decides that he wants to spend time with Morty and tries to fight Jessica; Principal Vagina intervenes to prevent him from injuring himself. As he is being removed, he sneezes, and a small bit of potion ends up in the punch bowl.

Back at home, Jerry is stressed about Beth being alone with Davin. Summer tries to comfort him, but Rick shows up and undermines him. Jerry goes out to visit the hospital and make sure Beth isn't cheating. Rick asks why Summer isn't at the dance, and she tells him she doesn't want to get the flu - it's flu season. Rick realizes that the potion could be spread by sneezing. At the dance, Morty is dancing with Jessica, but she tries to take things a little too far. Jessica's friends try to rescue him, but become overcome with the potion from the punch bowl. By this point, the potion-infected snot particles have made their way into the ventilation, and everyone at the dance has become obsessed with Morty. Rick arrives just in time to save Morty, and they flee to his vehicle. He has prepared an antidote based on Praying Mantis DNA, since mantises mate once and then try to decapitate their partner; they will deliver it with a massive cloud of contagious gas. But Rick accidentally gives them too much and they mutate into mantis people with an obsession for murdering Morty. The mantis DNA again spreads rapidly, turning the whole city into mantises - with the exception of Morty's family, who are immune, since the original potion was based around Morty's DNA. On the highway, Jerry is driving to the hospital when the people in the cars around him begin turning to mantis-people. He finds a dead cop and steals his rifle, using it to defend himself. Back home, Summer is alone as the house is invaded by mantis-people looking for Morty. Rick and Morty retreat to the desert, and prepare a new antidote that should neutralize all the ill-effects of the previous serums.

At the hospital, Beth and Davin finally finish up their horse surgery, and leave the sterilized room. Davin begins flirting with Beth, making her visibly uncomfortable. She attempts to leave but Davin stops her. Having been exposed to the outside air, he begins to become infected, and starts demanding to know where Morty is as he mutates. But Jerry shows up and kills Davin, saving Beth. Rick prepares to spread out the new antidote, patronizing Morty about how he caused the mess with his love potion. It works, at first; but after turning back to humans, everyone suddenly begins melting into horrifying fleshy masses. Jerry and Beth fight their way through the monsters and come across Summer. Beth blames Rick, and they go off to try save Morty. Rick concedes that he screwed the world up, but tells Morty he has one emergency backup solution.

Some time later, everything seems to have been fixed. Rick and Morty arrive back at the garage, and Rick once again asks Morty for the screwdriver. Suddenly, Rick's new machine explodes, killing them both instantly. A different Rick and Morty (the actual ones) show up in a portal; this is a parallel reality where Rick had fixed all the problems he created, but had the bad luck to die with Morty shortly thereafter. The real Rick explains that he and Morty are going to replace the dead versions of themselves, allowing them to continue their lives like nothing ever happened. They bury the bodies in the backyard. Morty tries to accept his 'new' family.

Back in the original dimension, Jerry, Beth, and Summer enjoy their lives in the post-apocalyptic landscape; Beth admits that with Rick gone, she is finally happy.

description: Sarah is troubled to learn that Andy Goode has rebuilt his computer the Turk II and entered it into a chess competition with a military contract as the winning prize. A Resistance fighter from the future takes matters into his own hands.

description: Desperate to save Derek Reese's life, John enlists the help of Charley Dixon but the paramedic struggles to come to terms with time travelers and Terminators. In the future Derek fights to survive when he's separated from his brother Kyle.
tags: ['opening recap', 'opening narration', 'paramedic', 'blood', 'flashback', 'future', 'post apocalypse', 'dystopia', 'resistance', 'soldier', 'brother brother relationship', 'kyle reese character', 'chained up', 'basement', 'cyborg', 'fire', 'garage', 'man from the future', 'time traveler', 'time travel', 'dragon in episode title', '2010s', '1990s']
synopsis_with_character_names:
Derek shakes on the kitchen table, the Terminators bullet hit his lung and the bullet is still in him. Charlie does his best to save him and demands answers. Derek screams and wants Cameron out of the room, Sarah orders her out.

As Derek beings to pass out, he remembers the future.

Derek sits next to his brother, Kyle Reese and share war stories about John Connor. Above them, Terminator battle machines roar by. The men head to street level to track the machines.

The men run through the streets hiding from flying Hunter Killers. The men see several Terminators dragging the engine from a 747. Kyle runs out for a closer look, but the men are spotted by a Hunter Killer. Derek turns to run and a Terminator grabs him.

Charlie pulls the bullet out of Dereks body and patches the wound.

Cameron stands with John. John asks Cameron if she knows who Derek is, hes searching for the answer he already knows. Cameron only recites tactical facts from Dereks military life.

Charlie tells Sarah that when he saw them on the news, he raced to Los Angeles to see if it was true. Sarah is hesitant to tell Charlie why she left eight years ago.

Derek wakes up in the back of a transport truck. A Terminator on board grabs Derek and knocks him out.

Charlie stands over the powered down Terminator from the jail, repeating what Sarah has told him. He tries to wrap his head around robots from the future and that Cameron is a machine. Cameron has prepared to destroy the Terminator using thermite. He watches Cameron sling the other Terminator over her shoulder and walk out back. Charlie tells John they could have trusted him years ago.

A Terminator throws water on Dereks face, grabs his arm, and brands him with the barcode tattoo. He calls for Kyle before he passes out. Later, Derek talks with another prisoner; they hear the sound of a piano. The man says there is a room in the basement, but they dont know what goes on there.

Cameron stands over Derek and Sarah walks in. Derek begins to cough up blood, Sarah screams for Charlie. Charlie stops the bleeding, but Derek needs blood. Charlie says Derek is AB-negative. John offers his blood, Charlie seems skeptical.

Derek tries to carve away the floor to free himself from the shackles. A Terminator drags Billy Wisher, one of Dereks team, back into the room but he appears comatose. Outside, Derek sees a Hunter Killer carrying away the 747 jet engine.

Sarah takes John aside and tells him it was a good idea bringing Charlie. John asks if Derek looks like his father. Sarah says everything except the eyes. John wants to tell Derek that hes family, but Sarah wont let him.

Billy wakes up and whispers to Derek. He tells Derek hes a liar, his real name is Andy Goodeand he created Skynet. Andy tells Derek he was part of a team, a team of fifteen people. He built a computer that became angry, and he begs forgiveness. A Terminator pulls Derek away.

A Terminator leads Derek into the basement, closer to the sounds of the piano. A door opens in the basement, Derek walks in and the door closes behind him.

In the garage, Cameron dissects the other Terminator, cutting away pieces of the fake-flesh.

John sits over Derek, putting his blood into his uncle. Charlie knows John is somehow related to Derek. Derek screams on the kitchen table, looking for Kyle.

In the future, Derek can barely stand as the machine locks him in shackles again. Derek lays on the floor, something horrible has happened to him. The light from another Hunter Killer shines down on them.

When the men wake up, the machines are gone, the mansion is silent. On the floor between them, is a hatchet. Derek grabs it and cuts himself free. The men hurry in the daylight along the rubble back to their underground camp. When they arrive, smoke and fire billows out. The Terminators have attacked the camp.

Charlie asks about Kyle, and realizes he is Johns father.

Derek walks in the tunnels underground, looking at the destruction. They hear people enter behind them and duck for cover. Its another Resistance group. The leader tells them that Kyle and John found a Skynet complex and tried to destroy it. John and Kyle went into the complex, but only John came out and ordered the complex destroyed. Derek demands to see John.

Charlie goes to the garage and sees Cameron dumping thermite on the endoskeleton. Charlie tells Cameron her behavior scares him. Cameron appears to take offense to Charlies words and tells him to leave. She drops a torch into the thermite.

Derek storms through a new camp with another Resistance fighter, trying to find John. Derek turns the corner and sees a Terminator, possibly Cameron, walking towards him. He grabs his pistol and tries to fire at her, but hes blocked by the Resistance fighter. The man tells Derek she has been reprogrammed. Derek is furious that Terminators are walking freely in the base, and wants to know what happened to his brother.

Later that night, screams ring out in the base. One of the reprogrammed Terminators has gone bad and is killing people. Derek fires his weapon, but it does little good. The Terminator tracks him down and as before he can kill him, the Cameron robot knocks it through a wall and destroys is with an explosive round.

Sarah confronts Cameron in the garage about what she said to Charlie. Sarah tells Cameron she cannot kill Charlie. Cameron tells Sarah the Terminators left had is missing, and Cameron swears to find it. Sarah leaves, and Cameron reveals the Terminators memory chip in her hand.

Charlie tells Sarah that Derek needs to take it easy, and offers his help in the future. Shes not trying to change her fate, shes trying to change Johns. Charlie tells Sarah that an Agent Kester contact him and is looking for her. She needs to be careful.

Sarah looks over and cleans assault rifles on the dining room table. John stands nearby, but says nothing. Sarah jumps up and embraces him.

Derek sits in a bunk in the shelter. The Cameron model machine tells him John wants to see him, and takes him to a secure section of the bunker. The door opens and Derek stands, amazed. A giant machine pulsates, using several 747 jet engines. Its the time machine.

In the present, John sits over Derek and tells him to rest easy.

In the future, Derek goes over the plan. Go to the past, set up a safe house. Derek knows this is their chance to save the future. He looks over to Andy. They must go back, and kill Andy.

John tells Derek about Kyles story. Kyle died fighting the machines to save John, and that Kyle was a hero.

A flashback to the chess tournament shows Derek opening the door to Andys room, firing two bullets, and then leaving.
